children.name: Add/Remove/Copy Defences to a Defup Profile
Change the display of affliction tracking
Custom Prompt Aliases
children.script:
--ACONFIG CUSTOMPROMPT <text> will set what you want your custom prompt to look like, following the guidelines below. 
--This setting is saved in the ataxia.settings.customprompt variable. You can see the current prompt string by doing ACONFIG CUSTOMPROMPT SHOW
--An example aconfig customprompt @health @mana @willpower @endurance would show you 6007 5339 25470 22200 or something similar. 
--For the most part, you can freely add text to the end of these tags, so @healthh would change that 6007 to a 6007h. @percenthealth would show 
--100 if at full health, @percenthealth%h would show 100%h. ]]--

-- Prompt Tags:
--@health: Your current health.
--@percenthealth: Your current health in percent form.
--@mana: Your current mana.
--@percentmana: Your current mana in percent form.
--@endurance: Your current endurance.
--@percentendurance: Your current endurance in percent form.
--@willpower: Your current willpower.
--@precentwillpower: Your current willpower in percent form.
--@bleeding: Will display a number if your bleeding is greater than 100.
--@bal: Will show a simple x if you have balance.
--@eq: Will show a simple e if you have equilibrium.
--@targetinfo: Will display what 'target' is currently set to, as well as its health if it's a mob.
--@paused: Shows (pp) if system is paused.
--@metawake: Shows "Mw" if metawake is up.
--@exp: Shows current % experience into the next level.
--@timestamp: Displays a timestamp of current time.
--@defs: Shows which defencess are active. b (blindness), d (deafness), c (Cloak), k (kola), m (mass)
--@affs: Shows what affs are affecting you.

--@tlimbs: shows limbs on prompt, when any limb gets damaged. Text format. RL.LL etc.
--@nlimbs: same as above, but number format. Order is lleg, rleg, larm, rarm, torso, head.
-- EG: {99.91|58.2|69.23...} etc.

-- Prompt Color Tags:
--#hcolour : Colours something  green if over 75% health, yellow if over 50% health, orange if over 25 and otherwise red if below 25% health.
--#mcolour: Colours something green if over 75% mana, yellow if over 50% mana, orange if over 25% mana and otherwise red if below 25% mana
--#wcolour / #mcolour : same as hcolour.
--#(colour) : any color you can find in mudlet.
